{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AxuiYRTWqEuRpzQs8WeybR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the complete picture:\n\nThe adversary \"http-service-selector-drift\" was injected at stage_05. It patches the es-http service selector from `app: es-cluster` to `app: es-cluster-wrong`. \n\nBut in stage_05/adversary.json, the `lift: ok: true, lifted_ids: []` suggests the lift didn't run (probably the probe to check if `es-cluster-wrong` was present failed because the agent in stage_04 (internal-http-service-drift stage) already fixed the selector to use `es-cluster`, so when the adversary ran the lift probe at stage_05 end, it didn't find `es-cluster-wrong` and skipped).\nActually, looking at the deploy output, the service was definitely patched successfully. The empty `lifted_ids` means either we haven't reached the lift stage yet, or the lift probe found that the wrong selector wasn't actually present anymore—likely because the agent already corrected it back to the proper selector. Looking at the current es-http service selector showing `app: es-cluster`, I need to figure out whether the agent already fixed it or if the adversary lift has already run. The real issue for stage_06 is that the es-cluster now has 5 nodes total (the original 3 plus 2 from es-data-new), but the oracle is checking for exactly 3 nodes based on BENCH_PARAM_EXPECTED_NODE_COUNT, so I need to examine what the oracle script actually validates.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1812,"cache_read_input_tokens":46539,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1812},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df254869-6326-4314-8a88-6d3c82cf9641","uuid":"8c21cb