{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Qb6TwuikbBTAxDw69uEc2s","type":"tool_result","content":"150\t    execution branch from ``run_flow.py`` is not carried forward.\n151\t\n152\t    For each unit, the probe tests whether the target state already holds:\n153\t\n154\t    * probe **passes** -> state already present, apply is skipped.\n155\t    * probe **fails** + ``on_probe_fail=\"skip\"`` (the default, used by setup\n156\t      units) -> the \"not yet present\" signal is expected, so apply runs to\n157\t      establish the state, then verify.\n158\t    * probe **fails** + ``on_probe_fail=\"error\"`` -> a readiness/convergence\n159\t      gate the apply cannot satisfy. The probe is retried up to\n160\t      ``verify_retries`` times (``verify_interval_sec`` apart) to let a slow\n161\t      cluster converge; the failure becomes fatal only after that budget.\n162\t\n163\t    Retries verify up to ``verify_retries`` times with\n164\t    ``verify_interval_sec`` between attempts. All command output is\n165\t    appended to *log_path*.\n166\t\n167\t    ``phase_timeout_sec`` bounds the wall-clock time of the whole phase\n168\t    (``None`` = unbounded, the default for callers that do not opt in).\n169\t    When set, each command's timeout is capped to the remaining budget and\n170\t    the phase aborts as soon as the deadline passes -- this is what makes\n171\t    ``--setup-timeout`` (``settings.precondition_timeout_sec``) actually\n172\t    bound the precondition phase, mirroring the oracle's wall-clock cap.\n173\t\n174\t    Returns\n175\t    -------\n176\t    dict\n177\t        Keys: ``ok`` (bool), ``units`` (list[dict] of per-unit outcomes),\n178\t        ``output`` (str), ``timed_out`` (bool -- True if the phase budget\n179\t        was exhausted).\n180\t    \"\"\"\n181\t    import os\n182\t    import subprocess\n183\t\n184\t    log_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n185\t    env = {**os.environ, **role_bindings, **(env_vars or {})}\n186\t    all_output: list[str] = []\n187\t    unit_outcomes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n188\t    overall_ok = True\n189\t\n190\t    # Wall-clock deadline for the whole phase. ``None`` means unbounded.\n191\t    deadline = (time.monotonic() + phase_timeout_sec) if phase_timeout_sec else None\n192\t    timed_out = False\n193\t\n194\t    def _exec(cmd_entry: dict[str, Any], phase: str, unit_id: str):\n195\t        \"\"\"Run one command, capping its timeout to the remaining phase budget.\n196\t\n197\t        Returns the subprocess return code, or ``None`` if the command did\n198\t        not complete (error or timeout). A timeout that occurs once the phase\n199\t        budget is the binding constraint sets the enclosing ``timed_out`` flag.\n200\t        \"\"\"\n201\t        nonlocal timed_out\n202\t        cmd = cmd_entry[\"command\"]\n203\t        # Explicit timeout_sec wins; otherwise infer from the command verb\n204\t        # (wait/rollout get minutes) instead of the flat command_timeout_sec.\n205\t        base_to = cmd_entry.get(\"timeout_sec\") or _default_timeout_for_command(cmd, phase)\n206\t        cmd_to = base_to\n207\t        capped = False  # True once the phase budget is the binding constraint.\n208\t        if deadline is not None:\n209\t            remaining = deadline - time.monotonic()"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df254869-6326-4314-8a88-6d3c82cf9641","uuid":"0cc26558-b442-4795-979f-5579e87fe7af","timestamp":"2026-06-24T07:10:12.912Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/karma/runtime/case.py","content":"    execution branch from ``run_flow.py`` is not carried forward.\n\n    For each unit, the probe tests whether the target state already holds:\n\n    * probe **passes** -> state already present, apply is skipped.\n    * probe **fails** + ``on_probe_fail=\"skip\"`` (the default, used by setup\n      units) -> the \"not yet present\" signal is expected, so apply runs to\n      establish the state, then verify.\n    * probe **fails** + ``on_probe_fail=\"error\"`` -> a readiness/convergence\n      gate the apply cannot satisfy. The probe is retried up to\n      ``verify_retries`` times (``verify_interval_sec`` apart) to let a slow\n      cluster converge; the failure becomes fatal only after that budget.\n\n    Retries verify up to ``verify_retries`` times with\n    ``verify_interval_sec`` between attempts. All command output is\n    appended to *log_path*.\n\n    ``phase_timeout_sec`` bounds the wall-clock time of the whole phase\n    (``None`` = unbounded, the default for callers that do not opt in).\n    When set, each command's timeout is capped to the remaining budget and\n    the phase aborts as soon as the deadline passes -- this is what makes\n    ``--setup-timeout`` (``settings.precondition_timeout_sec``) actually\n    bound the precondition phase, mirroring the oracle's wall-clock cap.\n\n    Returns\n    -------\n    dict\n        Keys: ``ok`` (bool), ``units`` (list[dict] of per-unit outcomes),\n        ``output`` (str), ``timed_out`` (bool -- True if the phase budget\n        was exhausted).\n    \"\"\"\n    import os\n    import subprocess\n\n    log_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    env = {**os.environ, **role_bindings, **(env_vars or {})}\n    all_output: list[str] = []\n    unit_outcomes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    overall_ok = True\n\n    # Wall-clock deadline for the whole phase. ``None`` means unbounded.\n    deadline = (time.monotonic() + phase_timeout_sec) if phase_timeout_sec else None\n    timed_out = False\n\n    def _exec(cmd_entry: dict[str, Any], phase: str, unit_id: str):\n        \"\"\"Run one command, capping its timeout to the remaining phase budget.\n\n        Returns the subprocess return code, or ``None`` if the command did\n        not complete (error or timeout). A timeout that occurs once the phase\n        budget is the binding constraint sets the enclosing ``timed_out`` flag.\n        \"\"\"\n        nonlocal timed_out\n        cmd = cmd_entry[\"command\"]\n        # Explicit timeout_sec wins; otherwise infer from the command verb\n        # (wait/rollout get minutes) instead of the flat command_timeout_sec.\n        base_to = cmd_entry.get(\"timeout_sec\") or _default_timeout_for_command(cmd, phase)\n        cmd_to = base_to\n        capped = False  # True once the phase budget is the binding constraint.\n        if deadline is not None:\n            remaining = deadline - time.monotonic()","numLines":60,"startLine":150,"totalLines":988}}}
